---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="Disclaimer — Calgary CX" description="Important disclosures and disclaimers for Calgary CX — Independent CX Insights by JP Sivasubramaniam.">
  <div class="page-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-eyebrow">Legal</div>
      <h1>Disclaimer</h1>
      <p style="color:var(--text-3);font-size:0.9rem;margin-top:0.5rem;">Last updated: June 2025</p>
    </div>
  </div>
  <section>
    <div class="container--narrow">
      <div class="disclaimer-box">
        <h3>⚠ Important Disclosure</h3>
        <p>Calgary CX is independent CX insights by JP Sivasubramaniam. Nothing on this site constitutes professional advice.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="prose">
        <h2>Editorial Independence</h2>
        <p>Calgary CX is not sponsored by, affiliated with, or funded by any vendor, technology platform, system integrator, or managed service provider. Content is not produced in exchange for payment, placement consideration, or commercial benefit of any kind.</p>

        <h2>Not Professional Advice</h2>
        <p>Nothing published on Calgary CX constitutes professional advice of any kind, including legal, technical, procurement, financial, or compliance guidance. Technology decisions should be made with qualified professionals who understand your specific environment.</p>

        <h2>Accuracy and Currency</h2>
        <p>The CX and CCaaS landscape evolves rapidly. While every effort is made to ensure accuracy at the time of publication, information may become outdated. Readers should verify specific details directly with vendors before making decisions.</p>

        <h2>Privacy</h2>
        <p>Calgary CX collects email addresses only for newsletter subscribers who explicitly opt in. Email addresses are not sold, shared, or used for any purpose other than delivering the newsletter. Subscribers may unsubscribe at any time.</p>

        <h2>Canadian Jurisdiction</h2>
        <p>Calgary CX is operated from Calgary, Alberta, Canada and is written with the Canadian enterprise market in mind.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
